We lost control as Spurs found a way to beat our press and went direct behind our defence knowing there is space to attack while we lost our way as we couldn't put our passes together and they were really smart beating our press. So we could only dig deep in that moment and try to hang on but with that midfield and the vulnerable defence due to Trent pushing up to midfield we can't get any foothold on the game. This is where Thiago would have been useful but unfortunately he isn't available so we can only do our best to stay in the game. Thankfully Jota scored right at the end thanks to a clever long kick from Alisson or else this would have been a huge shame not winning having been 3 goals up. Need to find a way to combat the vulnerability of Trent moving to midfield
